    thinking: "**Initiating the Review**\n\nI\'ve started by carefully analyzing the initial request. It involves a code review of the backend, focusing on optimization for Cloud Run deployment and Google internal access via AIS. This is the starting point for my thorough examination.\n\n\n**Addressing the Key Inquiry**\n\nI\'m now focused on the user\'s question regarding AIS sandbox compatibility. My analysis indicates that the proposed backend changes, specifically a shift to a full-stack architecture, will likely *enable* direct use within AIS, as opposed to hindering it. I am working on the assumption that the user wants to be able to use the secrets tab.\n\n\n**Clarifying Secrets Integration**\n\nI\'m now investigating the \"Secrets\" tab within AIS and its implications for our backend optimization. My understanding is that, with an Express-based full-stack approach, the `GEMINI_API_KEY` can be securely accessed via `process.env`. If the current setup is SPA based, then the secret would be on the client side, which is bad. The proposed backend change aligns well with the recommended approach for both AIS and Cloud Run. The requested code review now begins. I am going to look at `App.tsx` now.\n\n\n"
