    thinking: "**Analyzing Security Flaws**\n\nI\'ve pinpointed a major vulnerability: exposing the `GEMINI_API_KEY` through `vite.config.ts`\'s `define`. This is incredibly insecure, especially for deployment platforms like Cloud Run. The priority is shifting the Gemini API calls away from the client-side as the most critical architectural improvement.\n\n\n**Refactoring API Routes**\n\nI\'m now implementing the refactoring with Express. I\'m building a backend endpoint, `/api/generate`, to securely handle Gemini API calls. The `vite.config.ts` is getting cleaned up, removing the insecure `define` overrides and making sure the `GEMINI_API_KEY` is read from `process.env` in `server.ts`. This complete refactor secures the `GEMINI_API_KEY`, and will not negatively impact the sandbox.\n\n\n**Confirming Sandbox Compatibility**\n\nI\'m confirming that moving to an Express backend doesn\'t hinder the sandbox; in fact, it enhances it. By leveraging server-side environment variables via the \"Secrets\" tab, the setup is secure and the sandbox is still fully functional with an Express server and Vite middleware. I\'m preparing to review the backend code next, specifically focusing on Cloud Run deployment and internal Google access optimization. This will address the prompt directly.\n\n\n**Optimizing for Cloud Run**\n\nI\'m now prioritizing Cloud Run deployment and Google internal access optimization. I\'m focusing on the backend code, ensuring seamless operation within the Cloud Run environment. I\'m investigating best practices for Google internal access integration, which is paramount. I must also consider the sandbox environment. My priority is to identify and resolve any potential conflicts to ensure the sandbox continues to work seamlessly with the changes.\n\n\n**Answering User\'s Questions**\n\nI\'ve determined a complete full-stack refactor is the best approach to securing the `GEMINI_API_KEY`, following `<framework>` guidelines. I\'ve broken it down into steps: installing dependencies, creating `server.ts`, updating scripts, and refactoring `geminiService.ts` to divide frontend file processing and backend API calls. I can confidently say it *will* affect the current setup. I\'m ready to proceed immediately.\n\n\n"
